author: Joshua Axelrod
title: Watch: Martin O'Malley sings a Taylor Swift song
text:
Martin O'Malley's appearance on "The View" Tuesday concluded with the Democratic presidential candidate showing off his musical chops.
"Katy Perry, I'm told, is doing a benefit concert for one of my opponents in Iowa," O'Malley said. "So in response, I thought I'd offer this up for Taylor Swift."
O'Malley then brought out his guitar and began playing and singing Swift's "Bad Blood."
Related Story: http://www.washingtonexaminer.com/article/2574118/ Perry will be performing at the Jefferson-Jackson Dinner, an event for Hillary Clinton supporters, on Oct. 24 in Des Moines, Iowa.
More from the Washington Examiner Rubio on Crist: 'Some people can't live without' running for office "I'll let the voters in that area decide. I think they know we don't need more of Charlie Crist."
By Al Weaver â€¢ 10/20/15 5:24 PM O'Malley's song choice and Perry's endorsement of Clinton mirrors a publicly passive aggressive feud between Swift and Perry. It is widely believed that Swift wrote "Bad Blood" after a fallout with Perry, a former friend and member of Swift's "squad."
